[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Introduction"]
[Black "Middlegame Strategy 2: Hort, Vlastimil vs. Brunner, Lucas"]
[Result "*"]
[FEN "6r1/2p2bpp/2kb1p2/1ppNnP2/4P3/1P2N1B1/2P3PP/3R2K1 w - - 0 25"]
[SetUp "1"]

{ White's strategy to settle the knight on d5, paid out. } 25. Bxe5
{ Sometimes, the pair of knights should be preferred. } 25... fxe5
{ 25...Bxe5  Black would like to take back with the bishop, to stay active, but that fails due to Ne7+. }
26. Ra1
{ Another theme which we will witness throuhgout the course: the occupation of the a-file. }
26... Kb7 27. c4
{ If there was any doubt: the knight will not leave d5 without a fight! Due to the doubled pawns, the character of the position is closed. Favorable for the knights, bad for the bishops. }
27... c6 28. Nc3 Kb6 29. cxb5 { Regaining control over d5. } 29... cxb5 30.
Ned5+ Bxd5 31. Nxd5+ Kb7 32. Ra5 Kc6
{ 32...b4  33.Kf1  White walks towards c4. Black can try to get some counterplay with  33...c4  34.bxc4  Rc8  35.Rb5+  Ka7  36.Ne3  though White is better because of his material plus. }
33. Ra6+ Kd7 34. f6
{ 34.Kf2 !  this would be winning. For White it is easy to created a passed pawn on the kingside, supported by the strong knight and rook.  34...c4  35.b4 }
34... c4 35. bxc4 bxc4 { Black obtained counterplay though White won. } *

