{ Like in the main line, White is much better due to his space advantage. } 11.
Qxc3 Be7 12. Bf4
{ Black is in a squeeze and can't employ his bishops. Our play is rather simple by doubling our rooks on the d-file. A sample line which makes my heart pound faster, is  12...O-O  13.O-O  Re8  14.Rfe1  a5  15.Rad1  h6  16.Nd4  Bf8  17.e6 !!  fxe6  18.Nxe6  illustrating the deficiencies in Black's position. }
