{ Testing our opponent to the bone! The queen has to be moved, after which White follows up with Be3 and Nd4. }
17... Qf5
{ The much better queen move. Black is surviving for the moment, but with a king still in the center of the board, we are definitely still pressing. }
18. Be3 { Where should the Black king hide? } 18... c5
{ Black essentially has to play this move, otherwise Nd4 is coming with a much better position for White. }
19. b4 { The true idea behind 15. Rb1 is divulged. } 19... cxb4
{ Black's king will not find a shelter anymore. } 20. Qxb4
{ again, Black cannot castle. } 20... c5
{ This move closes the diagonal, preparing short castling. Please notice that White cannot take on b6, due to ...Bxc3. }
