f6 { This move closes down the long diagonal, possibly hinting at Bxe4 now. }
24. Rd4 { This move allows for an improvement of the knight with Ne4. } 24...
Ne7 25. Ne4
{ Things get tough for Black as an immediate result of White's active pieces, meanwhile he's also a pawn down. A highly promising continuation would be Be3-c1-b2, in order to attack f6. }
