Qd3
{ A move to remember. White not only makes room for the knight, but also prevents long castling. }
13... Ne7 { doesn't offer Black any salvation, after } 14. Nc3
{ The f6 square is our target. } 14... Qd7 15. Bg5
{ Black has the unpleasant choice between exchanging bishops or retreating to g7. }
15... Bg7
{ 15...Bxg5  16.Nxg5  was seemingly unattractive and 15...Bg7 was the lesser of the two evils. White, though, doesn't let go and seizes the initiative. }
16. Ne5
{ Black's position collapses, as Ne4 to f6 is coming, or if  16...Bxe5  17.Rxe5  O-O  18.Ne4!  when Black's king is too weak. }
