{ Black just wants to stop Ne6. } 16. Nc3 c5
{ Comprehensibly, Black is intending to regain the pawn. But his position cannot bear this opportunistic move. If  16...Ng4  17.Rad1  Nxe3  18.fxe3  is better for White - after all he is still a pawn up. As simple as that! }
17. Nf5 { Black's position collapses, as after } 17... Rxd3 18. Nxg7+ Kf8 19.
Nf5
{ White has numerous threats  (Nxe7 followed by Bxc5+ or Bg5 and Rd1)  and Black can't escape the pressure. }
