{ This is an improvement over the stem correspondence game, putting the pressure on and giving Black limited space to freely move his pieces.   14.f4  1-0 @@StartBracket@@40@@EndBracket@@ Gaujens, A @@StartBracket@@2565@@EndBracket@@ - Matisson, J @@StartBracket@@2274@@EndBracket@@ ICCF email 2001  14...Rh6  with the idea of  15..Rd6  , Black most likely being able to stand the strain by the exchange of rooks and castling long, is something we don't want! }
