14. e5 { White is ready for this advance: Black is not coordinated yet. } 14...
Qf5 15. Bc5
{ White settles on c5. Please note that Black can't chase away the bishop with ...b6, because of Qxa6+. }
15... Ng6 16. Na4
{ A highly interesting concept. The crucial square is the blockading square of the e-pawn: e6. By means of Na4 and Nc5, White's knight reaches the optimal square c5. }
16... Qf7 17. Rfe1
{ The pivotal point in the position is e6. Is Black capable of blocking it? }
17... Bxc5 18. Nxc5
{ I believe that White has everything to play for @@StartBracket@@and so thinks Lc0@@EndBracket@@ because Black has major concerns regarding the e5-pawn in conjunction with the blockade on e6. }
