8... Be7 9. Be3
{ At first sight, this bishop retreat may seem like not the most challenging choice. Besides, wouldn't we be glad to swap off one of Black's bishops, depriving him for the bishop pair @@StartBracket@@a powerful tool in the ending@@EndBracket@@? However, my enthusiasm for my initial choice of 9. Bxe7 quickly vanished after seeing Svidler's masterpiece, completely outplaying Naiditsch with the Black pieces.   9.Bxe7  I don't like this move since it gives Black the opportunity to rapidly develop his pieces. Especially after Svidler's straightforward win over Naiditsch, included in the model game section, I came to the conclusion that I should recommend 10. Be3 instead of 10. Bxe7.  9...Nxe7  10.Nc3  Bd7  Black has easy development.  11.Nde2   11.Nb3  here I couldn't find any advantage either.  11...Qxd1   11...O-O-O !?  is another plausible move for Black. This was featured in Morozevich's original game.  12.Qe2  g5  13.Qe3  b6  14.Qxg5  Rhg8  15.Qe3  Qg6  16.g3  h5  17.f3  f5  18.exf5  Nxf5 !  Black obtained a strong attack and went on to win. 0-1 @@StartBracket@@40@@EndBracket@@ Magem Badals, J @@StartBracket@@2520@@EndBracket@@ - Morozevich, A @@StartBracket@@2575@@EndBracket@@ Pamplona   12.Raxd1  b6  Black was doing fine in ½-½ @@StartBracket@@49@@EndBracket@@ Areshchenko, A @@StartBracket@@2664@@EndBracket@@ - Jakovenko, D @@StartBracket@@2736@@EndBracket@@ Khanty-Mansiysk 2009  11...O-O-O  12.Qc1   12.Qxd6  cxd6  Black has an easy game here. The d6-pawn is not a weakness as it can be easily defended.  12...Ng6  13.Qe3  Threatening Qa7  13...Kb8  14.Rad1  Qe7  15.f4  White has the better pawn structure, but Black is better here, strangely enough. All his pieces are well-positioned, and there are many ideas to hit the White central pawns and to create a kingside attack. For the rest, see the model game section. }
9... Nh6 10. Qd2 Qg6
{ Our opponent's set-up seems illogical. Specifically, the prospects of his knight are gloomy. }
11. f3
{ White is stabilizing his central pawn phalanx, meanwhile preventing Ng4. }
11... Bd7 12. Qa5
{ I would like to suggest this new idea, hitting c7 and luring Black into long castling. }
12... O-O-O 13. Nd2
{ I prefer the knight on d2, subsequently c4 or b3, rather than on c3. 13. Nc3 Was unclear in: 1-0 @@StartBracket@@36@@EndBracket@@ Naiditsch, A @@StartBracket@@2724@@EndBracket@@ - Maiorov, N @@StartBracket@@2548@@EndBracket@@ Bastia 2013. }
13... Rhe8 { Is not good, since after... } 14. Nc4 Qf6 15. a4
{ Unmistakably one of our main weapons in the Ruy-Lopez Exchange. When the opportunity is there, we don't hesitate to go for the attack. }
15... Kb8 16. Rfd1 Bc8 17. b4 *

