Qf2 { Luring the knight to d7, when d5 becomes vacant. } 16... Nd7 17. Nf4
{ The perfect position for the knight: hitting both d5 and e6. } 17... Ne5 18.
Ncd5
{ We have the better pawn structure and the slightly preferable chances, as the position is easier to play with White. For instance, }
18... Bd6 19. Rad1 Rae8 { Black is sitting on the fence. } 20. g4
{ The kingside expansion offers us serious attacking possibilities. Worth a try, to say the least. }
*

