11... Qe5
{ Here I would like to come with an improvement for White over the following correspondence game: 0-1 @@StartBracket@@43@@EndBracket@@ Dehaybe, A - Schwarte, J LSS email 2007 }
12. Be3 Bd6 { Hitting h2. } 13. g3 h5
{ Black starts a counter-attack on the h-file. Primarily, White will keep the kingside closed. Secondarily, he starts on offense of his own on the queenside. }
14. Rab1 h4 15. Bf4 { Optimally using the bad position of the queen. } 15...
Qh5 16. g4
{ Of course, White keeps the h-file closed thwarting Black's attack. } 16...
Qf7 17. Bxd6 cxd6 18. b4
{ Now it's White's turn to attack the enemy king! The next moves will be 'smooth sailing' after c4 and b5. Black should fear his near future! }
