Ng6 18. f4 { An insidious trap has been built in by this move. } 18... Bd6
{ There you go. The most obvious move of Black allows a nasty tactic. } 19.
Nxc6 bxc6 20. Qxc6
{ Now it becomes clear that the bishop is misplaced. In our main line, Black could play here Rd6! }
20... Qe6 21. Rac1 Ne7 22. Qxa6+ Kd7 23. Qa4+
{ Gradually it comes to the surface that there is no safe passage to the kingside for the king. }
23... c6 24. e5
{ Winning the piece back, maintaining all the privileges built up. } 24... fxe5
25. fxe5 Qxe5 26. Bf4 { White is winning. } *

