17... Re5 { Preparing both e5 and Rde8. } 18. Nd2
{ Again, Black cannot rid himself of the d6-pawn by playing d6-d5. After 19.Nc4, Black is losing material. }
18... Qf7 19. b3
{ Renewing the threat and parrying Qxa2. White prepares for the knight leap to c4. }
19... d5 20. c4
{ Hitting d5 while the Black king is still slightly exposed on c8. } 20... dxc4
21. Nxc4 Re6 { Preventing Nd6+. } 22. Nb6+ { Creating a stepping-stone on d7. }
22... Kc7 23. Rxd8 Kxd8 24. Rd1+
{ There is no way of stopping the White rook coming in. } 24... Ke8 25. Qg3
{ White's attack is unstoppable. } *

