{ The king is crossing over to a safer side of the board. White should be very accurate with his move order, as after 14. Be3, Black gets the chance to activate its knight.   14.Be3 ?!  Ng6 !  The difference with 14. Kf1 emerges: White has no time to play 15.Nf5, because of the knight fork on h4.  15.Kf1  Nh4  16.Qe2  Since the queen should retreat blocking the route of the king, Black obtained sufficient counterplay.  16...O-O-O }
14... Ng6 { Bad timing, as after } 15. Qf5
{ The knight is pinned, whereas the king is stuck on e8. } *

