{ White is has the more pleasant position, despite  being a pawn down. 1-0 @@StartBracket@@47@@EndBracket@@ Szabo,V @@StartBracket@@2386@@EndBracket@@ - Szabo, M @@StartBracket@@2232@@EndBracket@@ LSS email 2011. This is because of his control of the central and light squares. The pawn on f6 is weak and can be taken under siege with Be3-d2-c3. }
