10... Bd7
{ Has appeared 10 times in practice and should be a move we reckon with. } 11.
d4 Ng6
{ This happened 6 times! All the White players went for 12.Nc4, while there was a far better try! }
12. Bg5 Qe6 13. d5
{ White is capable of locking in the queen on the middle of the board! A fine combination. }
13... cxd5 14. Nd4
{ Quite an artificial way to open the e-file! But it works! Please be aware of the fact that the queen has no squares to go to. }
14... exd4 15. exd5
{ The White rook is in his element on e1. Black loses his queen. } *

