15... Nxg2 16. Qxh3 Nxe1 { when Rxe1 fails, due to Rxd2 and Qxg5. } 17. f4 Nxc2
18. f5
{ The point! The mighty pawns are reigning over the board, and, where should the queen go to? }
18... Qh6 19. Nxf7 Qh7 { The only square for the queen: a sad conclusion. } 20.
Nxd8 Nxa1 21. Ne6
{ Together with the pawns, it puts the Black pieces in a headlock. } 21... Nxb3
22. Qxb3
{ Black's queen and rook can't be involved in play, whereas White's 3 pieces find their way to the enemy king. }
