{ Former world champion Alexander Alekhine was the first who made the Black line flourish with this strong follow-up. }
8. Nbd2
{ A solid move. The knight defends f3 and can join the defensive forces. } 8...
Ne7
{ The knight is on his road to g6 and eventually h4. White has to watch out! }
9. Re1
