15. e6
{ Before unpinning himself, White throws the cat amongst the pigeons. The concept of giving this pawn up in order to inflict as much as possible damage to Black's structure, can be considered a ' desperado' . }
15... f6
{ Black is keeping his structure intact. Nonetheless, White can put the screws to his opponent with the following plan. }
16. Re1
{ Unpinning is part of the job for us in this line. The knight is free to hop now. Apart from that, this move contains some venom, since after 16..Nf4 17.Nf3 Nxe6 18.e5! White obtains active play along the e-file. }
