12... Bxc5 13. e5 fxe5 14. Nxe5 Qf6 15. Nd3
{ The best spot for the knight is on the blockading square. } 15... Bd6 16. Ne4
{ Your engine may suggest this as an OK line for Black. But as we all know, the engine is never afraid for any attacks. We follow up with Re1; it is just too dangerous for Black. }
16... Qf5 17. Re1 Kd8 18. Nxd6
{ There were more promising plans for White, for instance a2-a4 to open the a-file. }
18... cxd6 19. Bf4 { Again, a2-a4 was a sound alternative. } 19... Nf7 20. Qa3
{ Black's king is surrounded, and the chances on a good result are diminishing move by move. }
*

