12... Bxc5 13. e5 f5
{ A more realistic approach for Black: he keeps the files closed. } 14. e6 Bc8
{ In spite of the material deficit, we can be very happy with the outcome of the opening. I I feel sorry for the Black king. }
15. Qc2 { Indirectly attacking c6. } 15... Qd5 16. Nb3
{ With the attack on c5 and h6. } 16... Bd6 17. Bxh6
{ Doing even more harm to Black's king. No safe havens left to set sail to. }
17... gxh6 18. Nbxd4
{ Black's poor king's position results into fine attacking prospects for us. }
18... c5 19. Nxf5 { Black's position is visibly crumbling. } 19... O-O 20. Nxd6
cxd6 21. e7
{ We use this small pawn as a distractor of the opponent's forces. It gives us the space to collect as many as possible Black pawns. }
21... Re8 22. Rfe1 { Now our rooks are deployed. } 22... Ra7 23. Rad1 Qf7 24.
Rxd6 { The remnants of Black's position: in complete disorder. } 24... Raxe7
25. Rxe7 Qxe7 26. Qxc5 { leads to a winning position for White. } *

