{ How to follow up on White's elementary positional play on the kingside? } 28.
h5 Nd6 29. h6 { Breaking up the pawn chain. } 29... fxg5 30. Rxg5
{ When the black g-pawn disappears from the g-file, White will get all he ever longed for: 2 connected passed pawns. }
30... g6 31. fxg6 hxg6 32. Rxg6 Ref8 33. Rg7 Rxg7 34. hxg7 Rg8 35. Rg2 Ne8 36.
Be5 { The rest was child's play. } 36... Ke6 37. Kf4 Kf7 38. Kf5 *

