{ Though being a piece down, White intends can afford here a quiet move. } 17.
Rd2
{ After this quiet, ominous move, Black is in serious trouble. He has to deal with 2 threats: Nf7+ and eventually Rxe2. }
17... Ke6 18. Rxe2 { The knight cannot be taken surprisingly. } 18... Rd7
{ 18...Kxd6  19.Bf4+ !  Kd7  20.Rd1+  Kc8  21.Red2  21...b5  22.Rd8+  Kb7  23.Bxc7  Kxc7  24.R1d7+  Kb6  25.Rxe7  White is winning material and the game. }
19. Nc4 Rd1+
{ The pin looks threatening, but actually White can chase the rook away from the back rank. }
20. Kh2 Ng6 21. Ne3
{ The Black rook has to retreat from the first rank, whereafter Black lacks sufficient counterplay for the pawn. }
